Registered Cultivars

Registered Cultivars

ABS maintains the current list of all registered cultivars.

Since 1955, the American Begonia Society has been the International Registration Authority for the naming of cultivars of begonias.

Over the years, there have been over 1,000 cultivars registered with ABS. The History and Background of ABS Cultivar Registration provides a brief history of the process and the people behind Cultivar Registration.

Registered cultivars are also published in The Begonian, with a full description and photo of the Begonia.

The current list is below.
